ADDITIONAL DESIGN & BRANDING TERMS

The MIT license above covers the source code (logic, architecture, component
structure). The following terms apply separately to the visual design and brand
assets of this project:

1. BRAND ASSETS — The "Cybersage" name, logo, wordmark, color palette, custom
   cursor system, and all visual identity elements are proprietary and are NOT
   covered by the MIT license. All rights reserved.

2. DESIGN — The specific UI/UX design, layout compositions, motion design, and
   overall aesthetic of cybersage.dev are the original creative work of the
   author. You may NOT replicate the visual design or present it as your own
   portfolio, product, or commercial work.

3. LEARNING — You are explicitly welcome to study the architecture, patterns,
   and implementation techniques for personal learning and to inform your own
   original work.

In short: learn from the code freely. Do not clone the design or impersonate
the brand.
